I'm using cantera 1.5 with Matlab, with imported kinetics mechanisms
in Chemkin  format, so I'm using the "ck2cti" function from the DOS
command line to convert to .cti files. I've had success with one
mechanism, but with another, I'm encountering a troubling error. While
the ck2cti function executes successfully from the DOS prompt, when
using "importPhase" from the Matlab prompt, I get the following error:

Cantera Error!
Procedure: getRateCoefficient
Error: negative or zero A coefficient for reaction 145

Error in ==> solution.m
on line 37 ==> k = Kinetics(node, t);

Error in ==> importPhase.m
on line 7 ==> s = Solution(file, name);

The troubling thing is that the A coefficient for this reaction is
properly defined as a positive number, and in fact, the ck2cti.log
file correctly interprets this positive A coefficient. For some
reason, some Cantera function is incorrectly reading the .cti file or
the .cti file was made incorrectly despite a correct ck2cti.log. Any
insights?

Patrick Caton
Stanford University Advanced Energy Systems Lab
